01/07/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government should continue to intensify reforms in defence, economy, judiciary, respect for minorities and the fight against organised crime, said NATO Parliamentary Assembly President Douglas Bereuter. 
On Wednesday (30 June), he met in Skopje with Prime Minister Hari Kostov, Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski, Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and Parliament Speaker Ljupco Jordanovski. 
Macedonia was the first stop of his tour of the Adriatic Charter countries. 
He will also visit Albania and Croatia.
In other news, a two-day regional workshop for control of small and light weapons opens Thursday in Skopje. 
Experts from eight Southeast European countries will participate. 
Meanwhile, Turkey has said it will donate 426,000 euros worth of equipment to the army barracks in Djorce Petrov. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 30/06/04)
